    "The hyperplane is defined by w • x + b = 0, and instances are classified based on the sign of f (x).",
    "An instance is considered normal if f (x) > 0 and anomalous if f (x) < 0.",
    "Correlation matrix for binary class labels.",
    "The figure 10 showcases the decision boundary of an SVM (Support Vector Machine) model used to classify data into two distinct categories: \"Anomaly\" and \"Normal. \"",
    "The data points are plotted in two-dimensional space where the red points are from anomaly class and the points in purple color are from normal class."
